Schedule the Script:

On Windows (using Task Scheduler):

Open Task Scheduler.
Create a new task and specify the script's location to run. Set the trigger to your desired schedule (e.g., daily, weekly) and provide the necessary authentication and access permissions.
On Linux/macOS (using cron jobs):

Open your crontab file by running crontab -e in your terminal.

Add an entry to schedule the script. For example, to run it daily at 2:00 PM, add the following line:
